'''Aphidicolin''' is defined as a tetracyclic [[diterpene]] [[antibiotic]] with antiviral and antimitotical properties.  Aphidicolin is a reversible [[Enzyme inhibitor|inhibitor]] of [[eukaryote|eukaryotic]] nuclear [[DNA]] replication. It blocks the cell cycle at early [[S phase]]. It is a specific inhibitor of [[DNA polymerase]] A,D in eukaryotic cells and in some viruses and an [[apoptosis]] inducer in [[HeLa]] cells.
<br>Natural aphidicolin is a secondary metabolite of the fungus ''[[Nigrospora oryzae]]''.<ref>[http://www.fermentek.co.il/aphidicolin.htm Aphidicolin product page] from [[Fermentek]]</ref>

