'''Guanacastepene A''' is a compound showing promising [[antibiotic]] activity. It is a [[diterpene]] that was extracted with [[hexane]] from a [[Costa Rica]]n [[fungus]] (CR115), found on the branches of the ''[[Daphnopsis Americana]]'' tree and purified by [[chromatography]].<ref>{{cite journal | author = Brady, Sean F.; Singh, Maya P.; Janso, Jeff E.; Clardy, Jon | title = Guanacastepene, a Fungal-Derived Diterpene Antibiotic with a New Carbon Skeleton | journal = Journal of the American Chemical Society | year = 2000 | volume = 122 | issue = 9 | pages = 2116–2117 | doi = 10.1021/ja993835m}}</ref>
