'''Streptolydigin''' (Stl) is an [[antibiotic]] that works by inhibiting [[nucleic acid]] chain elongation by binding to [[RNA polymerase]], thus inhibiting [[RNA]] synthesis inside a [[cell (biology)|cell]].<ref>{{cite PMID |16122422}}</ref><ref>{{cite PMID |16167380}}</ref><ref>{{cite PMID |17581591}}</ref> Streptolydigin inhibits bacterial RNA polymerase and eukaryotic [[RNA polymerase III]]. It has antibacterial activity against a number of [[Gram positive]] [[bacteria]].
