{{antibiotic-stub}}

A '''cell envelope antibiotic''' is an antibacterial that acts primarily at the level of the [[cell envelope]].

Examples include [[cycloserine]], [[penicillin]], and [[polymyxin B]].<ref name="urlAntibiotics that affect the cell envelope">{{cite web |url=http://pathmicro.med.sc.edu/fox/antibiotics1.htm |title=Antibiotics that affect the cell envelope |work= |accessdate=}}</ref>

