'''Brilacidin''' (formerly '''PMX-30063''') is an [[antibiotic]] that works by disrupting bacterial cell membranes, mimicking [[defensin]]s from [[innate immunity]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biocentury.com/products/pmx-30063|title=brilacidin (formerly PMX-30063)|work=BioCentury BCIQ|accessdate=2013-09-19|publisher=BioCentury Publications}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Butler|first=Mark S|author2=Cooper, Matthew A|title=Antibiotics in the clinical pipeline in 2011|journal=The Journal of Antibiotics|date=18 May 2011|volume=64|issue=6|pages=413–425|doi=10.1038/ja.2011.44}}</ref>
