{{more footnotes|date=August 2013}}

[[image:Tachyplesins.png|thumb|Tachyplesin I and Tachyplesin II]]

'''Tachyplesin''' is an [[antimicrobial peptides|antimicrobial peptide]] isolated from the [[horseshoe crab]]. It has a molecular weight of 2.36 kDa and the amino acid sequence KWCFRVCYRGICYRRCR.<ref>http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3141410</ref>

==Notes==
[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1666545 Direct virus inactivation of tachyplesin I and its isopeptides from horseshoe crab hemocytes]

