{{antibiotic-stub}}

'''Bambermycin''' (Flavomycin) is a complex of [[antibiotic]]s obtained from ''[[Streptomyces bambergiensis]]'' used as a food additive for [[poultry]] and [[Domestic pig|swine]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.drugs.com/vet/flavomycin-4.html | title = Flavomycin 4 | publisher = drugs.com}}</ref> The complex consists mainly of moenomycins A and C.<ref name=PubChem>{{PubChem| 6433554}}</ref>
Flavomycin is effective against [[Gram-positive bacteria]], but it does not have significant action against ''[[Lactobacillus]]'', ''[[Bifidobacterium]]'', and other protective bacteria.<ref name=Merck>{{cite document | url = http://www.merck-animal-health-usa.com/binaries/intp1069_FLAVOMYCIN_tcm96-86660.pdf | title = Product Information Sheet: Flavomycin®4 (bambermycins) | publisher = Merck Animal Health }}</ref> Its [[mechanism of action]] involves inhibition of [[bacterial wall]] synthesis.<ref name=Merck/>
Synonyms included flavofosfolipol, gainpro, menomycin, and flavophospholipol.<ref name=PubChem/>
==References== {{reflist}}
